{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":226,"text":"So I want to talk to you about two things tonight."},{"time":4048,"text":"Number one:"},{"time":6332,"text":"Teaching surgery and doing surgery"},{"time":9648,"text":"is really hard."},{"time":11781,"text":"And second,"},{"time":13365,"text":"that language is one of the most profound things"},{"time":15864,"text":"that separate us all over the world."},{"time":19182,"text":"And in my little corner of the world,"},{"time":21099,"text":"these two things are actually related,"},{"time":23049,"text":"and I want to tell you how tonight."}]},{"cues":[{"time":24981,"text":"Now, nobody wants an operation."},{"time":28987,"text":"Who here has had surgery?"},{"time":32926,"text":"Did you want it?"},{"time":34249,"text":"Keep your hands up if you wanted an operation."},{"time":35807,"text":"Nobody wants an operation."},{"time":37899,"text":"In particular, nobody wants an operation"},{"time":40961,"text":"with tools like these through large incisions"},{"time":46449,"text":"that cause a lot of pain,"},{"time":48424,"text":"that cause a lot of time out of work or out of school,"},{"time":51956,"text":"that leave a big scar."},{"time":54207,"text":"But if you have to have an operation,"},{"time":57109,"text":"what you really want is a minimally invasive operation."},{"time":59640,"text":"That's what I want to talk to you about tonight --"},{"time":61672,"text":"how doing and teaching this type of surgery"},{"time":64406,"text":"led us on a search"},{"time":65873,"text":"for a better universal translator."}]},{"cues":[{"time":68407,"text":"Now, this type of surgery is hard,"},{"time":70750,"text":"and it starts by putting people to sleep,"},{"time":74274,"text":"putting carbon dioxide in their abdomen,"},{"time":76391,"text":"blowing them up like a balloon,"},{"time":78207,"text":"sticking one of these sharp pointy things into their abdomen --"},{"time":83396,"text":"it's dangerous stuff --"},{"time":86943,"text":"and taking instruments and watching it on a TV screen."},{"time":91586,"text":"So let's see what it looks like."},{"time":93553,"text":"So this is gallbladder surgery."},{"time":95319,"text":"We perform a million of these a year"},{"time":97351,"text":"in the United States alone."},{"time":99569,"text":"This is the real thing. There's no blood."},{"time":101619,"text":"And you can see how focused the surgeons are,"},{"time":104753,"text":"how much concentration it takes."},{"time":107268,"text":"You can see it in their faces."},{"time":108952,"text":"It's hard to teach, and it's not all that easy to learn."},{"time":115459,"text":"We do about five million of these in the United States"},{"time":117437,"text":"and maybe 20 million of these worldwide."}]},{"cues":[{"time":122724,"text":"All right, you've all heard the term:"},{"time":125557,"text":"\"He's a born surgeon.\""},{"time":127355,"text":"Let me tell you, surgeons are not born."},{"time":130755,"text":"Surgeons are not made either."},{"time":134492,"text":"There are no little tanks where we're making surgeons."},{"time":137832,"text":"Surgeons are trained one step at a time."},{"time":142287,"text":"It starts with a foundation, basic skills."},{"time":146139,"text":"We build on that and we take people, hopefully, to the operating room"},{"time":150904,"text":"where they learn to be an assistant."},{"time":152672,"text":"Then we teach them to be a surgeon in training."},{"time":154806,"text":"And when they do all of that for about five years,"},{"time":157738,"text":"they get the coveted board certification."},{"time":161104,"text":"If you need surgery, you want to be operated on"},{"time":163738,"text":"by a board-certified surgeon."},{"time":166222,"text":"You get your board certificate,"},{"time":168206,"text":"and you can go out into practice."},{"time":170549,"text":"And eventually, if you're lucky, you achieve mastery."}]},{"cues":[{"time":174816,"text":"Now that foundation is so important"},{"time":178848,"text":"that a number of us"},{"time":180749,"text":"from the largest general surgery society in the United States, SAGES,"},{"time":184316,"text":"started in the late 1990s a training program"},{"time":187182,"text":"that would assure that every surgeon who practices minimally invasive surgery"},{"time":191533,"text":"would have a strong foundation of knowledge and skills"},{"time":196115,"text":"necessary to go on and do procedures."},{"time":198800,"text":"Now the science behind this is so potent"},{"time":202899,"text":"that it became required by the American Board of Surgery"},{"time":206683,"text":"in order for a young surgeon to become board certified."},{"time":210233,"text":"It's not a lecture, it's not a course,"},{"time":214018,"text":"it's all of that plus a high-stakes assessment."},{"time":217416,"text":"It's hard."},{"time":219650,"text":"Now just this past year,"},{"time":222784,"text":"one of our partners, the American College of Surgeons,"},{"time":225850,"text":"teamed up with us to make an announcement"},{"time":227712,"text":"that all surgeons should be FLS (Fundamentals of Laparoscopic Surgery)-certified"},{"time":231182,"text":"before they do minimally invasive surgery."}]},{"cues":[{"time":234266,"text":"And are we talking about just people here in the U.S. and Canada?"},{"time":237710,"text":"No, we just said all surgeons."},{"time":239683,"text":"So to lift this education and training worldwide"},{"time":244382,"text":"is a very large task,"},{"time":245632,"text":"something I'm very personally excited about as we travel around the world."},{"time":249574,"text":"SAGES does surgery all over the world, teaching and educating surgeons."},{"time":254266,"text":"So we have a problem, and one of the problems is distance."},{"time":258305,"text":"We can't travel everywhere."},{"time":260538,"text":"We need to make the world a smaller place."},{"time":263356,"text":"And I think that we can develop some tools to do so."},{"time":266039,"text":"And one of the tools I like personally is using video."}]},{"cues":[{"time":270022,"text":"So I was inspired by a friend."},{"time":272472,"text":"This is Allan Okrainec from Toronto."},{"time":274721,"text":"And he proved"},{"time":277326,"text":"that you could actually teach people to do surgery"},{"time":281572,"text":"using video conferencing."},{"time":284272,"text":"So here's Allan teaching an English-speaking surgeon in Africa"},{"time":288505,"text":"these basic fundamental skills"},{"time":291055,"text":"necessary to do minimally invasive surgery."},{"time":293772,"text":"Very inspiring."},{"time":295372,"text":"But for this examination, which is really hard,"},{"time":299138,"text":"we have a problem."},{"time":301955,"text":"Even people who say they speak English,"},{"time":304555,"text":"only 14 percent pass."},{"time":307072,"text":"Because for them it's not a surgery test,"},{"time":309088,"text":"it's an English test."}]},{"cues":[{"time":312963,"text":"Let me bring it to you locally."},{"time":314572,"text":"I work at the Cambridge Hospital."},{"time":316239,"text":"It's the primary Harvard Medical School teaching facility."},{"time":319522,"text":"We have more than 100 translators covering 63 languages,"},{"time":324838,"text":"and we spend millions of dollars just in our little hospital."},{"time":330022,"text":"It's a big labor-intensive effort."},{"time":331797,"text":"If you think about the worldwide burden"},{"time":335863,"text":"of trying to talk to your patients --"},{"time":337722,"text":"not just teaching surgeons, just trying to talk to your patients --"},{"time":340357,"text":"there aren't enough translators in the world."},{"time":343505,"text":"We need to employ technology to assist us in this quest."},{"time":349471,"text":"At our hospital we see everybody from Harvard professors"},{"time":352638,"text":"to people who just got here last week."},{"time":355072,"text":"And you have no idea how hard it is"},{"time":357357,"text":"to talk to somebody or take care of somebody you can't talk to."},{"time":360289,"text":"And there isn't always a translator available."}]},{"cues":[{"time":363189,"text":"So we need tools."},{"time":367552,"text":"We need a universal translator."},{"time":371230,"text":"One of the things that I want to leave you with as you think about this talk"},{"time":375639,"text":"is that this talk is not just about us preaching to the world."},{"time":381156,"text":"It's really about setting up a dialogue."},{"time":383705,"text":"We have a lot to learn."},{"time":385556,"text":"Here in the United States we spend more money per person"},{"time":390056,"text":"for outcomes that are not better than many countries in the world."},{"time":393906,"text":"Maybe we have something to learn as well."}]},{"cues":[{"time":397289,"text":"So I'm passionate about teaching these FLS skills all over the world."},{"time":401772,"text":"This past year I've been in Latin America, I've been in China,"},{"time":405156,"text":"talking about the fundamentals of laparoscopic surgery."},{"time":408889,"text":"And everywhere I go the barrier is:"},{"time":412421,"text":"\"We want this, but we need it in our language.\""},{"time":417055,"text":"So here's what we think we want to do:"},{"time":419972,"text":"Imagine giving a lecture"},{"time":422389,"text":"and being able to talk to people in their own native language simultaneously."},{"time":427385,"text":"I want to talk to the people in Asia, Latin America, Africa, Europe"},{"time":433073,"text":"seamlessly, accurately"},{"time":437793,"text":"and in a cost-effective fashion using technology."},{"time":442074,"text":"And it has to be bi-directional."},{"time":443702,"text":"They have to be able to teach us something as well."}]},{"cues":[{"time":446489,"text":"It's a big task."},{"time":447889,"text":"So we looked for a universal translator; I thought there would be one out there."},{"time":450955,"text":"Your webpage has translation, your cellphone has translation,"},{"time":454906,"text":"but nothing that's good enough to teach surgery."},{"time":460106,"text":"Because we need a lexicon. What is a lexicon?"},{"time":462572,"text":"A lexicon is a body of words that describes a domain."},{"time":466671,"text":"I need to have a health care lexicon."},{"time":469156,"text":"And in that I need a surgery lexicon."},{"time":472757,"text":"That's a tall order. We have to work at it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":477012,"text":"So let me show you what we're doing."},{"time":478805,"text":"This is research -- can't buy it."},{"time":481106,"text":"We're working with the folks at IBM Research from the Accessibility Center"},{"time":485589,"text":"to string together technologies to work towards the universal translator."},{"time":490522,"text":"It starts with a framework system"},{"time":492656,"text":"where when the surgeon delivers the lecture"},{"time":495388,"text":"using a framework of captioning technology,"},{"time":498555,"text":"we then add another technology to do video conferencing."},{"time":502971,"text":"But we don't have the words yet, so we add a third technology."},{"time":506456,"text":"And now we've got the words,"},{"time":509106,"text":"and we can apply the special sauce: the translation."},{"time":513657,"text":"We get the words up in a window and then apply the magic."},{"time":518037,"text":"We work with a fourth technology."},{"time":520321,"text":"And we currently have access to eleven language pairs."},{"time":524305,"text":"More to come as we think about trying to make the world a smaller place."},{"time":528806,"text":"And I'd like to show you our prototype"},{"time":531455,"text":"of stringing all of these technologies that don't necessarily always talk to each other"},{"time":536288,"text":"to become something useful."}]},{"cues":[{"time":539955,"text":"Narrator: Fundamentals of Laparoscopic Surgery."},{"time":543751,"text":"Module five: manual skills practice."},{"time":547364,"text":"Students may display captions in their native language."}]},{"cues":[{"time":554647,"text":"Steven Schwaitzberg: If you're in Latin America,"},{"time":556396,"text":"you click the \"I want it in Spanish\" button"},{"time":558281,"text":"and out it comes in real time in Spanish."},{"time":561913,"text":"But if you happen to be sitting in Beijing at the same time,"},{"time":564747,"text":"by using technology in a constructive fashion,"},{"time":568080,"text":"you could get it in Mandarin or you could get it in Russian --"},{"time":571346,"text":"on and on and on, simultaneously without the use of human translators."},{"time":576812,"text":"But that's the lectures."}]},{"cues":[{"time":579012,"text":"If you remember what I told you about FLS at the beginning,"},{"time":581863,"text":"it's knowledge and skills."},{"time":584880,"text":"The difference in an operation"},{"time":587163,"text":"between doing something successfully and not"},{"time":591763,"text":"may be moving your hand this much."},{"time":595230,"text":"So we're going to take it one step further;"},{"time":597530,"text":"we've brought my friend Allan back."}]},{"cues":[{"time":599663,"text":"Allan Okrainec: Today we're going to practice suturing."},{"time":604764,"text":"This is how you hold the needle."},{"time":606762,"text":"Grab the needle at the tip."},{"time":612259,"text":"It's important to be accurate."},{"time":614717,"text":"Aim for the black dots."},{"time":618550,"text":"Orient your loop this way."},{"time":621999,"text":"Now go ahead and cut."},{"time":626584,"text":"Very good Oscar. I'll see you next week."}]},{"cues":[{"time":630472,"text":"SS: So that's what we're working on"},{"time":633338,"text":"in our quest for the universal translator."},{"time":636321,"text":"We want it to be bi-directional."},{"time":638405,"text":"We have a need to learn as well as to teach."},{"time":642606,"text":"I can think of a million uses for a tool like this."},{"time":646622,"text":"As we think about intersecting technologies --"},{"time":649372,"text":"everybody has a cell phone with a camera --"},{"time":651772,"text":"we could use this everywhere,"},{"time":653988,"text":"whether it be health care, patient care,"},{"time":656071,"text":"engineering, law, conferencing, translating videos."},{"time":660556,"text":"This is a ubiquitous tool."}]},{"cues":[{"time":662956,"text":"In order to break down our barriers,"},{"time":665155,"text":"we have to learn to talk to people,"},{"time":666922,"text":"to demand that people work on translation."},{"time":670922,"text":"We need it for our everyday life,"},{"time":673272,"text":"in order to make the world a smaller place."},{"time":676106,"text":"Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":677806,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}